==English==
===Noun===
'''solvolysis'''
#{{chemistry}} any [[reaction]], between a [[solute]] and its [[solvent]], in which one or more [[bond]]s of the solute are [[broken]]; specifically a [[substitution]], [[elimination]] or [[fragmentation]] reaction in which the solvent is the [[nucleophile]]
===Related terms===
*[[alcoholysis]]
*[[hydrolysis]]

